N:clawteam
D:Route ClawTeam operator requests into the right mode before touching commands: manual team control, one-command template launch, monitoring/recovery, or provider/runtime profile setup. Use when the user explicitly wants the ClawTeam task/inbox/worktree swarm workflow for parallel developer work, fullstack delivery, product/ops research teams, marketing/content studios, or game and simulation squads. Not for generic multi-agent routing when `jeo`, `omc`, `omx`, `ohmg`, `vibe-kanban`, or simple subtask delegation already fit.
G:clawteam multi-agent swarm orchestration tmux git-worktree autonomous python routing

U[6]:
  Explicit ClawTeam team/task/inbox/worktree workflows
  Parallel developer workflow and fullstack delivery teams
  Product/ops, marketing/content, and game/simulation squads using ClawTeam
  Monitoring existing teams with board/team/task/inbox commands
  Provider/model setup via preset/profile flows
  Honest route-outs for generic orchestration requests

S[4]{n,action,details}:
  1,Manual team control,bash clawteam team spawn-team my-team -d "Build the auth module" -n leader && clawteam spawn tmux claude --team my-team --agent-name architect --task "Design the API schema" && clawteam task create my-team "Design the API schema" -o architect && clawteam board attach my-team
  2,Launch a template,bash clawteam template list && clawteam launch hedge-fund --team fund1 --goal "Analyze AAPL, MSFT, NVDA for Q2 2026" && clawteam board attach fund1
  3,Monitor or recover,bash clawteam team status my-team && clawteam board show my-team && clawteam task list my-team --status blocked && clawteam inbox peek my-team
  4,Provider/runtime setup,bash clawteam preset list && clawteam preset generate-profile moonshot-cn claude --name claude-kimi && clawteam profile doctor claude && clawteam spawn tmux --profile claude-kimi --team my-team --agent-name researcher --task "Compare onboarding flows"
